    "In the older literature (notably in the well-known book by Schneider et al. 1992) cosmologies with total density different from ρ cr are also considered, as are more general considerations of the angular-diameter distances.",
    "The expressions given here are restricted to cosmologies that are spatially flat (or equivalently, have mean density equal to ρ cr), but this is a standard assumption made in nearly all of the recent literature.",
    "Yet another quantity which one occasionally meets in lensing formalism is the conformal time.",
    "A conformal time interval is given by (1 + z) -1 dt.",
    "Using the conformal time, one can trace light rays as if in a static universe."
